   "source": [
    "## Modules\n",
    "\n",
    "Modules are Python files containing code (functions, variables, classes) that can be imported and used in other Python files."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Importing Built-in Modules"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import the entire module\n",
